00:19:33.830 --> 00:19:36.080 align:middle line:90%
and subconsciousness?

00:19:36.080 --> 00:19:40.760 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Well, there
actually is no subconscious

00:19:40.760 --> 00:19:43.520 align:middle line:90%
if you get rid of fear.

00:19:43.520 --> 00:19:49.160 align:middle line:84%
It's a little different twist
on the Freudian model of mind,

00:19:49.160 --> 00:19:53.133 align:middle line:84%
and that is that fear
is where we create

00:19:53.133 --> 00:19:54.800 align:middle line:84%
the subconscious to
deal with the things

00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:56.630 align:middle line:84%
that we don't really
want to deal with.

00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:59.690 align:middle line:84%
The things we push below
the surface, things

00:19:59.690 --> 00:20:01.820 align:middle line:90%
that are uncomfortable for us.

00:20:01.820 --> 00:20:04.670 align:middle line:84%
Those things tend to
be in the subconscious.

00:20:04.670 --> 00:20:07.340 align:middle line:84%
And if you've developed
the subconscious,

00:20:07.340 --> 00:20:10.430 align:middle line:84%
then it becomes that
unknown part of your life

00:20:10.430 --> 00:20:12.530 align:middle line:84%
that just kind of
urges you to do things,

00:20:12.530 --> 00:20:14.800 align:middle line:84%
and you're not quite sure
where that comes from.

00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:15.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:20:15.230 --> 00:20:16.370 align:middle line:90%
Or eats away at you, too.

00:20:16.370 --> 00:20:17.703 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: Or eats away at you.

00:20:17.703 --> 00:20:21.650 align:middle line:84%
But if you don't have that
fear, and if you are love--

00:20:21.650 --> 00:20:24.270 align:middle line:84%
and when you don't have fear,
you are love, by the way.

00:20:24.270 --> 00:20:26.600 align:middle line:90%
That's just the way that works.

00:20:26.600 --> 00:20:29.960 align:middle line:84%
At that point, you
are a whole person.

00:20:29.960 --> 00:20:31.580 align:middle line:90%
You understand all of you.

00:20:31.580 --> 00:20:35.330 align:middle line:84%
You don't have part of you
that is hidden from you.

00:20:35.330 --> 00:20:37.340 align:middle line:90%
You're aware of all of yourself.

00:20:37.340 --> 00:20:39.893 align:middle line:90%
You're aware of your needs.

00:20:39.893 --> 00:20:41.060 align:middle line:90%
You're aware of your hunger.

00:20:41.060 --> 00:20:42.808 align:middle line:90%
You're aware of your sexuality.

00:20:42.808 --> 00:20:45.350 align:middle line:84%
You're aware of what's going on
in your life and who you are.

00:20:45.350 --> 00:20:47.030 align:middle line:90%
You are authentic.

00:20:47.030 --> 00:20:51.350 align:middle line:84%
And in that stage, you
don't have a subconscious.

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:55.550 align:middle line:84%
You have an awareness
from top to bottom of who

00:20:55.550 --> 00:20:56.630 align:middle line:90%
and what you are.

00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:59.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is the
Theory of Everything?

00:20:59.610 --> 00:21:02.690 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Well, that
is the fundamental model

00:21:02.690 --> 00:21:07.100 align:middle line:90%
that I published in 2003.

00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:09.410 align:middle line:84%
It's a theory of
consciousness that also turned

00:21:09.410 --> 00:21:11.600 align:middle line:90%
into a theory of physics.

00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:17.807 align:middle line:84%
But what it does is it explains
everything that is objective.

00:21:17.807 --> 00:21:19.640 align:middle line:84%
That would be science,
you know, the quantum

00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:21.650 align:middle line:90%
mechanics and relativity.

00:21:21.650 --> 00:21:24.390 align:middle line:84%
And it explains everything
that's subjective,

00:21:24.390 --> 00:21:25.640 align:middle line:90%
and that's a little different.

00:21:25.640 --> 00:21:27.700 align:middle line:84%
And people kind of have
to double-take on that.

00:21:27.700 --> 00:21:29.080 align:middle line:90%
Everything's subjective.

00:21:29.080 --> 00:21:33.340 align:middle line:84%
That means that your
feelings, your situation,

00:21:33.340 --> 00:21:37.870 align:middle line:84%
the level of your happiness,
or your misery, or pain.

00:21:37.870 --> 00:21:42.710 align:middle line:84%
All of that has an explanation
why it is you feel that way.

00:21:42.710 --> 00:21:45.040 align:middle line:84%
And this model,
then, will explain

00:21:45.040 --> 00:21:46.300 align:middle line:90%
why did you feel that way?

00:21:46.300 --> 00:21:50.710 align:middle line:84%
So it explains all the
subjective experiences we have.

00:21:50.710 --> 00:21:52.210 align:middle line:84%
And when I say
explains it, it means

00:21:52.210 --> 00:21:55.300 align:middle line:84%
it hangs it on a
logical structure

00:21:55.300 --> 00:21:56.740 align:middle line:90%
so that it makes sense.

00:21:56.740 --> 00:21:59.140 align:middle line:84%
We can see where it
comes from, and why

00:21:59.140 --> 00:22:02.015 align:middle line:84%
it's like that, and where
we need to go to change it.

00:22:02.015 --> 00:22:02.890 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:22:02.890 --> 00:22:05.620 align:middle line:84%
This theory that
you came up with,

00:22:05.620 --> 00:22:08.680 align:middle line:84%
was it one of those
aha moments for you?

00:22:08.680 --> 00:22:12.280 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: It was a very, very
long string of aha moments.

00:22:12.280 --> 00:22:16.120 align:middle line:84%
It started with Monroe
at Monroe Laboratories.

00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:17.860 align:middle line:90%
I was the physicist there.

00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:19.250 align:middle line:90%
I worked with Dennis Mennerich.

00:22:19.250 --> 00:22:23.380 align:middle line:84%
He was a EE there,
and we were Bob's lab.

00:22:23.380 --> 00:22:26.240 align:middle line:84%
We made the lab, and we were
the Guinea pigs in the lab.

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:27.040 align:middle line:90%
And I--

00:22:27.040 --> 00:22:27.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Did it all.

00:22:27.980 --> 00:22:28.780 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: Yeah.

00:22:28.780 --> 00:22:31.320 align:middle line:84%
My purpose was to explain
why things happened.

00:22:31.320 --> 00:22:34.030 align:middle line:84%
You know, the physicist,
the theoretician.

00:22:34.030 --> 00:22:36.240 align:middle line:84%
Dennis was to help
design the equipment

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:38.930 align:middle line:90%
and also work with me.

00:22:38.930 --> 00:22:43.210 align:middle line:84%
But I started doing research
there, and experiments there.

00:22:43.210 --> 00:22:45.760 align:middle line:84%
And slowly, I
thought I understood

00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:47.620 align:middle line:90%
how consciousness worked.

00:22:47.620 --> 00:22:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Then I got the aha moment that
understanding consciousness

00:22:51.250 --> 00:22:53.600 align:middle line:84%
gave me an understanding
of physics.

00:22:53.600 --> 00:22:59.560 align:middle line:84%
So that model just came
together over 35 to 40 years

00:22:59.560 --> 00:23:04.720 align:middle line:84%
of research, and it was
based on my experience.

00:23:04.720 --> 00:23:07.090 align:middle line:84%
When I was working
in the non-physical,

00:23:07.090 --> 00:23:09.700 align:middle line:84%
in the out-of-body state
doing research there,

00:23:09.700 --> 00:23:11.890 align:middle line:90%
I came up with a set of facts.

00:23:11.890 --> 00:23:15.040 align:middle line:84%
Things that I knew
were true, for me.

00:23:15.040 --> 00:23:16.750 align:middle line:90%
You know, this is subjective.

00:23:16.750 --> 00:23:19.990 align:middle line:84%
Facts in the world
of consciousness.

00:23:19.990 --> 00:23:22.630 align:middle line:84%
I also am a physicist,
so I had a set of facts

00:23:22.630 --> 00:23:25.270 align:middle line:84%
in the objective world as
well that I understood,

00:23:25.270 --> 00:23:30.640 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to create a
single, overarching theory that

00:23:30.640 --> 00:23:32.650 align:middle line:90%
explained all of those facts.

00:23:32.650 --> 00:23:37.210 align:middle line:84%
The facts that I had developed
in the 30 years of out-of-body

00:23:37.210 --> 00:23:39.460 align:middle line:84%
and doing research
in consciousness,

00:23:39.460 --> 00:23:41.980 align:middle line:84%
and all the facts I
knew as a physicist.

00:23:41.980 --> 00:23:43.720 align:middle line:90%
So that's how the model came.

00:23:43.720 --> 00:23:47.470 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it's a big toe,
because it's not a little toe

00:23:47.470 --> 00:23:48.610 align:middle line:90%
like Einstein worked on.

00:23:48.610 --> 00:23:50.710 align:middle line:84%
That would just be
the objective world.

00:23:50.710 --> 00:23:53.020 align:middle line:84%
It's the objective and
the subjective world.

00:23:53.020 --> 00:23:58.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How much of this is a
product of one's imagination?

00:23:58.750 --> 00:24:01.150 align:middle line:90%
Or it's the real deal?

00:24:01.150 --> 00:24:03.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Well, that
is an excellent question.

00:24:03.740 --> 00:24:06.220 align:middle line:84%
You see, when you're in
the subjective world,

00:24:06.220 --> 00:24:09.620 align:middle line:84%
you get information
from several sources.

00:24:09.620 --> 00:24:11.110 align:middle line:84%
One of those is
your imagination.

00:24:11.110 --> 00:24:12.140 align:middle line:90%
We're consciousness.

00:24:12.140 --> 00:24:14.750 align:middle line:84%
We get to make up
information as well.

00:24:14.750 --> 00:24:16.570 align:middle line:84%
The other is the larger
conscious system,

00:24:16.570 --> 00:24:18.970 align:middle line:84%
or it could be from some
other consciousness,

00:24:18.970 --> 00:24:20.920 align:middle line:84%
because we're all
netted in consciousness.

00:24:20.920 --> 00:24:23.590 align:middle line:90%
All conscious beings are netted.

00:24:23.590 --> 00:24:26.860 align:middle line:84%
So you never really
know for sure

00:24:26.860 --> 00:24:29.470 align:middle line:84%
which one of those three
paths your information

00:24:29.470 --> 00:24:30.940 align:middle line:90%
is coming from.

00:24:30.940 --> 00:24:32.810 align:middle line:90%
Information defines the reality.

00:24:32.810 --> 00:24:34.480 align:middle line:90%
It could be from any of those.

00:24:34.480 --> 00:24:38.530 align:middle line:84%
The only way to tell is
with a lot of experience.

00:24:38.530 --> 00:24:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And you need to find things
in the consciousness world

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:46.460 align:middle line:84%
that you can then verify
in the physical world.

00:24:46.460 --> 00:24:48.910 align:middle line:84%
In other words, things
like remote viewing.

00:24:48.910 --> 00:24:50.080 align:middle line:90%
Like healing.

00:24:50.080 --> 00:24:53.860 align:middle line:84%
All of the paranormal
things that people do.

00:24:53.860 --> 00:24:55.510 align:middle line:90%
Precognitive dreams.

00:24:55.510 --> 00:24:59.020 align:middle line:84%
You have to be able
to do enough of this

00:24:59.020 --> 00:25:03.190 align:middle line:84%
to convince yourself that
what you're getting is real.

00:25:03.190 --> 00:25:05.640 align:middle line:84%
It's not just something
that's in your imagination.

00:25:05.640 --> 00:25:08.380 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't really
attach to anything real.

00:25:08.380 --> 00:25:12.610 align:middle line:84%
So that's what we spent a decade
at Monroe Laboratories doing.

00:25:12.610 --> 00:25:15.190 align:middle line:84%
We spent almost all
of our time doing

00:25:15.190 --> 00:25:16.600 align:middle line:90%
things that were evidential.

00:25:16.600 --> 00:25:18.980 align:middle line:84%
Things that you could
then look up later and say

00:25:18.980 --> 00:25:22.210 align:middle line:84%
does this information I got
correspond with the information

00:25:22.210 --> 00:25:23.650 align:middle line:90%
that I know that's here?

00:25:23.650 --> 00:25:26.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you uncover
things that you didn't expect?

00:25:26.440 --> 00:25:29.080 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: I uncovered lots
of things I didn't expect.

00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:32.590 align:middle line:90%
One of them was that when--

00:25:32.590 --> 00:25:36.137 align:middle line:84%
as a physicist, and as
particularly a young guy,

00:25:36.137 --> 00:25:37.720 align:middle line:84%
I was in my 20s when
all this started.

00:25:37.720 --> 00:25:38.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez, you were a baby.

00:25:38.740 --> 00:25:40.032 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: I was a baby, yeah.

00:25:40.032 --> 00:25:42.580 align:middle line:84%
I first went out to Monroe
Laboratory working with him

00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:45.550 align:middle line:90%
and I was like 28?

00:25:45.550 --> 00:25:46.775 align:middle line:90%
27, 28 years old.

00:25:46.775 --> 00:25:48.025 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good for you, though.

00:25:48.025 --> 00:25:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: So I had
this idea that religion

00:25:51.100 --> 00:25:53.890 align:middle line:90%
was mostly nonsense.

00:25:53.890 --> 00:25:57.520 align:middle line:84%
That it was mostly made
out of fearful people who

00:25:57.520 --> 00:26:00.550 align:middle line:84%
were looking for
answers to big questions

00:26:00.550 --> 00:26:02.350 align:middle line:90%
that didn't have answers.

00:26:02.350 --> 00:26:03.530 align:middle line:90%
And I discounted it.

00:26:03.530 --> 00:26:04.330 align:middle line:90%
I was arrogant.

00:26:04.330 --> 00:26:06.970 align:middle line:84%
You know, most young
physicists in their 20s

00:26:06.970 --> 00:26:08.080 align:middle line:90%
are pretty arrogant.

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:10.370 align:middle line:90%
So I had this arrogant attitude.

00:26:10.370 --> 00:26:12.730 align:middle line:84%
So I thought that
religion was mostly

00:26:12.730 --> 00:26:14.710 align:middle line:90%
nonsense and a lot of belief.

00:26:14.710 --> 00:26:18.490 align:middle line:84%
And then one of my big
things that I didn't expect

00:26:18.490 --> 00:26:23.170 align:middle line:84%
was that most of what I
learned about consciousness

00:26:23.170 --> 00:26:25.330 align:middle line:84%
and the nature of
reality was stuff

00:26:25.330 --> 00:26:29.590 align:middle line:84%
that people had known
for the last 5,000 years.

00:26:29.590 --> 00:26:33.880 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, the Buddha said
that reality was an illusion.

00:26:33.880 --> 00:26:35.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, he didn't use the
words virtual reality,

00:26:35.940 --> 00:26:37.680 align:middle line:90%
but it fits perfectly.

00:26:37.680 --> 00:26:43.170 align:middle line:84%
And sages, and people who
have explored inner space

00:26:43.170 --> 00:26:46.050 align:middle line:84%
come to all the same
conclusions that I

00:26:46.050 --> 00:26:50.550 align:middle line:84%
came to as a physicist doing
research in the nonphysical.

00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:53.160 align:middle line:84%
It all boiled down to
pretty much the same thing.

00:26:53.160 --> 00:26:56.040 align:middle line:84%
And then I realized that
religion, for the most part,

00:26:56.040 --> 00:26:58.410 align:middle line:90%
was based on fundamental truths.

00:26:58.410 --> 00:26:59.850 align:middle line:90%
That is the way it is.

00:26:59.850 --> 00:27:01.630 align:middle line:90%
That's the way the world works.

00:27:01.630 --> 00:27:05.920 align:middle line:84%
But there's also lots
of dogma, and creeds,

00:27:05.920 --> 00:27:09.590 align:middle line:84%
and my god's better than
your god sort of thing.

00:27:09.590 --> 00:27:11.910 align:middle line:84%
There is a lot of
nonsense involved in it,

00:27:11.910 --> 00:27:15.660 align:middle line:84%
but the fundamentals,
the basic ideas

00:27:15.660 --> 00:27:19.740 align:middle line:84%
that are common
to most religions,

00:27:19.740 --> 00:27:20.970 align:middle line:90%
are fundamental truth.

00:27:20.970 --> 00:27:22.020 align:middle line:90%
That is the way it is.

00:27:22.020 --> 00:27:24.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tom, what exactly
is quantum mechanics?

00:27:24.750 --> 00:27:26.910 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Well, quantum
mechanics was actually

00:27:26.910 --> 00:27:29.230 align:middle line:84%
created because
of one experiment,

00:27:29.230 --> 00:27:31.540 align:middle line:84%
and that was the
double-slit experiment.

00:27:31.540 --> 00:27:33.540 align:middle line:84%
And quantum mechanics
was invented

00:27:33.540 --> 00:27:37.080 align:middle line:84%
to explain the results
of this experiment.

00:27:37.080 --> 00:27:39.750 align:middle line:84%
And in this
experiment, the results

00:27:39.750 --> 00:27:43.320 align:middle line:84%
were such that they
defied materialism.

00:27:43.320 --> 00:27:46.710 align:middle line:90%
They defied Newtonian mechanics.

00:27:46.710 --> 00:27:49.980 align:middle line:84%
So Einstein came
to the conclusion,

00:27:49.980 --> 00:27:54.780 align:middle line:84%
actually got a Nobel Prize for
it, that light was a particle.

00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:58.770 align:middle line:84%
And we had known, scientists
had known for almost 100 years,

00:27:58.770 --> 00:28:00.690 align:middle line:90%
that light was a wave.

00:28:00.690 --> 00:28:02.760 align:middle line:84%
So now there was
this discrepancy,

00:28:02.760 --> 00:28:06.070 align:middle line:84%
because particles and waves
don't act the same way.

00:28:06.070 --> 00:28:12.810 align:middle line:10%
So the scientists at that time,
now this is like 1915 to 1925,

00:28:12.810 --> 00:28:16.410 align:middle line:10%
that decade is when
most of this took place,

00:28:16.410 --> 00:28:20.880 align:middle line:10%
they found a way to
take light particles,

00:28:20.880 --> 00:28:25.200 align:middle line:10%
photons, and send
them at a barrier that

00:28:25.200 --> 00:28:27.120 align:middle line:10%
had two slits cut in it.

00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:30.480 align:middle line:10%
Because they knew that if
they shined a coherent light

00:28:30.480 --> 00:28:32.940 align:middle line:10%
on those two slits,
they would get what's

00:28:32.940 --> 00:28:34.590 align:middle line:10%
called a diffraction pattern.

00:28:34.590 --> 00:28:36.540 align:middle line:10%
There'd be places where
there was no light,

00:28:36.540 --> 00:28:38.820 align:middle line:10%
and other places
where there was light,

00:28:38.820 --> 00:28:40.950 align:middle line:10%
because light would go
through both the slits,

00:28:40.950 --> 00:28:44.640 align:middle line:10%
interfere with itself, and
make this diffraction pattern.

00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:46.740 align:middle line:84%
Well, when they put
particles through there,

00:28:46.740 --> 00:28:49.890 align:middle line:84%
particles are just supposed
to go through a slit

00:28:49.890 --> 00:28:52.290 align:middle line:84%
and then hit the
screen behind the slit,

00:28:52.290 --> 00:28:53.715 align:middle line:84%
because that's
what particles do.

00:28:53.715 --> 00:28:54.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But not this time.

00:28:54.840 --> 00:28:56.520 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: But not this time.

00:28:56.520 --> 00:28:59.730 align:middle line:84%
This time, when they just
sent the particles through one

00:28:59.730 --> 00:29:03.600 align:middle line:84%
at a time, those particles
rearranged themselves

00:29:03.600 --> 00:29:08.770 align:middle line:84%
in the same diffraction pattern
that a light wave would make.

00:29:08.770 --> 00:29:12.600 align:middle line:84%
And then, to find out really
what was going on at those two

00:29:12.600 --> 00:29:16.830 align:middle line:84%
slits, they put detectors
there so they could tell when

00:29:16.830 --> 00:29:18.870 align:middle line:90%
a photon went through a slit.

00:29:18.870 --> 00:29:21.720 align:middle line:84%
And when they did
that, the photons just

00:29:21.720 --> 00:29:25.140 align:middle line:84%
piled up behind the slits
like a good particle

00:29:25.140 --> 00:29:26.660 align:middle line:90%
is supposed to do.

00:29:26.660 --> 00:29:31.950 align:middle line:84%
So now they had this problem of
when they looked at the data,

00:29:31.950 --> 00:29:35.670 align:middle line:84%
at the slit, they got
particle pattern, if you will.

00:29:35.670 --> 00:29:37.500 align:middle line:90%
Piles of particles.

00:29:37.500 --> 00:29:42.930 align:middle line:84%
And when they didn't, they got
a wave, which was the same as--

00:29:42.930 --> 00:29:44.920 align:middle line:84%
which produced a
diffraction pattern.

00:29:44.920 --> 00:29:46.920 align:middle line:84%
So there was no way to
explain that, because you

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:50.610 align:middle line:84%
see these particles, Newton
told us, were supposed

00:29:50.610 --> 00:29:53.340 align:middle line:84%
to travel in a straight
line unless acted upon

00:29:53.340 --> 00:29:54.910 align:middle line:90%
by an external force.

00:29:54.910 --> 00:29:57.170 align:middle line:90%
It's like Newton's second law.

00:29:57.170 --> 00:29:59.520 align:middle line:84%
That's so long ago, I'm
not sure I got that right,

00:29:59.520 --> 00:30:00.180 align:middle line:90%
but it's one of Newton's.

00:30:00.180 --> 00:30:02.222 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You were there
with Newton, weren't you?

00:30:02.222 --> 00:30:03.270 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: Almost.

00:30:03.270 --> 00:30:04.900 align:middle line:90%
It was one of Newton's laws.

00:30:04.900 --> 00:30:07.360 align:middle line:84%
And anyhow, that's not
what was happening.

00:30:07.360 --> 00:30:09.690 align:middle line:84%
There were no external
forces on these particles,

00:30:09.690 --> 00:30:12.330 align:middle line:84%
but yet they weren't
traveling in a straight line.

00:30:12.330 --> 00:30:16.830 align:middle line:84%
They were rearranging themselves
in this very particular wave

00:30:16.830 --> 00:30:17.880 align:middle line:90%
pattern.

00:30:17.880 --> 00:30:21.930 align:middle line:84%
So quantum mechanics was
born to answer that question.

00:30:21.930 --> 00:30:24.090 align:middle line:90%
How can we understand this?

00:30:24.090 --> 00:30:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And what they decided was that
there really were no particles.

00:30:28.890 --> 00:30:31.350 align:middle line:90%
There's only probable particles.

00:30:31.350 --> 00:30:33.930 align:middle line:84%
A particle might be
somewhere and might not.

00:30:33.930 --> 00:30:36.840 align:middle line:84%
So particles only
existed as probability.

00:30:36.840 --> 00:30:38.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So they weren't sure.

00:30:38.110 --> 00:30:38.370 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: Yeah.

00:30:38.370 --> 00:30:40.412 align:middle line:84%
Well, they're saying that
there are no particles.

00:30:40.412 --> 00:30:41.860 align:middle line:90%
There's just probability.

00:30:41.860 --> 00:30:43.680 align:middle line:84%
And if we look at the
probability of where

00:30:43.680 --> 00:30:47.730 align:middle line:84%
these particles go,
then we can do the math,

00:30:47.730 --> 00:30:49.710 align:middle line:84%
and look at the
probability function,

00:30:49.710 --> 00:30:52.260 align:middle line:84%
and we get this
diffraction pattern.

00:30:52.260 --> 00:30:54.870 align:middle line:84%
So that was where quantum
mechanics was born.

00:30:54.870 --> 00:30:56.910 align:middle line:84%
And then of course in
the next 100 years,

00:30:56.910 --> 00:30:59.400 align:middle line:84%
it was about 100
years ago, they got

00:30:59.400 --> 00:31:01.800 align:middle line:84%
more and more sophisticated,
and quantum mechanics

00:31:01.800 --> 00:31:03.570 align:middle line:84%
grew and developed,
and now it's one

00:31:03.570 --> 00:31:09.390 align:middle line:84%
of our most productive, most
successful theories ever,

00:31:09.390 --> 00:31:11.340 align:middle line:84%
because it's almost
always right.

00:31:11.340 --> 00:31:13.343 align:middle line:90%
It makes the right predictions.

00:31:13.343 --> 00:31:14.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tom, you
produced a video

00:31:14.760 --> 00:31:18.530 align:middle line:84%
on how you believe we
can change the world.

00:31:18.530 --> 00:31:22.260 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: If you'd
like to change the world,

00:31:22.260 --> 00:31:27.000 align:middle line:84%
if you're tired of all of the
greed and abuse, people using

00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:31.890 align:middle line:84%
people, corporations using their
customers, and their suppliers,

00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:35.430 align:middle line:84%
and everybody else to
accumulate more and more wealth.

00:31:35.430 --> 00:31:38.700 align:middle line:84%
If you really don't like
the self-centeredness

00:31:38.700 --> 00:31:44.490 align:middle line:84%
and the nastiness that we
find here instead of the love,

00:31:44.490 --> 00:31:48.480 align:middle line:84%
and peace, and caring that
we'd like to find here,

00:31:48.480 --> 00:31:52.200 align:middle line:84%
well, the way you go
about changing the world

00:31:52.200 --> 00:31:54.900 align:middle line:90%
is by changing yourself.

00:31:54.900 --> 00:31:56.700 align:middle line:84%
All the negative
things that you see

00:31:56.700 --> 00:32:02.200 align:middle line:84%
going on in the world that are
upsetting to you are symptoms.

00:32:02.200 --> 00:32:07.530 align:middle line:84%
They're symptoms of a low
quality of consciousness.

00:32:07.530 --> 00:32:10.980 align:middle line:84%
They're symptoms of a high
entropy consciousness.

00:32:10.980 --> 00:32:13.830 align:middle line:10%
Once we understand that
this is a virtual reality,

00:32:13.830 --> 00:32:16.080 align:middle line:10%
once these experiments
are done and help

00:32:16.080 --> 00:32:19.530 align:middle line:10%
verify that this is a virtual
reality, once we as a people,

00:32:19.530 --> 00:32:22.830 align:middle line:10%
or as a race,
understand our purpose

00:32:22.830 --> 00:32:27.330 align:middle line:10%
as consciousness is to grow
up and evolve our quality,

00:32:27.330 --> 00:32:30.640 align:middle line:10%
then people will
begin to change.

00:32:30.640 --> 00:32:34.290 align:middle line:84%
And as people change,
these symptoms

00:32:34.290 --> 00:32:38.490 align:middle line:84%
of low quality of consciousness
will change all by themselves.

00:32:38.490 --> 00:32:40.410 align:middle line:84%
You see, it's the
quality of consciousness

00:32:40.410 --> 00:32:42.070 align:middle line:90%
that's the problem.

00:32:42.070 --> 00:32:45.300 align:middle line:10%
Not the dictator, not
the president and CEO

00:32:45.300 --> 00:32:48.540 align:middle line:10%
of the corporation that's
abusing people, not

00:32:48.540 --> 00:32:49.950 align:middle line:10%
the politicians.

00:32:49.950 --> 00:32:52.500 align:middle line:84%
Those are symptoms
of the problem.

00:32:52.500 --> 00:32:55.730 align:middle line:84%
The problem is low
quality of consciousness.

00:32:55.730 --> 00:32:59.640 align:middle line:84%
Doing these experiments, showing
that this is a virtual reality,

00:32:59.640 --> 00:33:03.570 align:middle line:84%
understanding what that
means in terms of who we are,

00:33:03.570 --> 00:33:07.710 align:middle line:84%
and what's important and what's
not in terms of growing up

00:33:07.710 --> 00:33:10.200 align:middle line:90%
and decreasing our entropy.

00:33:10.200 --> 00:33:12.690 align:middle line:10%
Increasing the quality
of our consciousness.

00:33:12.690 --> 00:33:14.290 align:middle line:90%
Becoming love.

00:33:14.290 --> 00:33:16.720 align:middle line:90%
Caring about other people.

00:33:16.720 --> 00:33:19.150 align:middle line:84%
This is what will
change the world.

00:33:19.150 --> 00:33:21.780 align:middle line:84%
If we want to live in a
kinder, gentler world,

00:33:21.780 --> 00:33:26.663 align:middle line:84%
we have to change
ourselves first.

00:33:26.663 --> 00:33:29.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I love that picture
of those politicians punching

00:33:29.080 --> 00:33:30.550 align:middle line:90%
each other out.

00:33:30.550 --> 00:33:33.790 align:middle line:84%
Must've been an
emotional meeting.

00:33:33.790 --> 00:33:37.930 align:middle line:84%
Can we change ourselves,
or is this something

00:33:37.930 --> 00:33:39.717 align:middle line:90%
that is built within us?

00:33:39.717 --> 00:33:41.800 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Oh, of course
we can change ourselves.

00:33:41.800 --> 00:33:43.240 align:middle line:90%
We can grow up.

00:33:43.240 --> 00:33:44.920 align:middle line:90%
We can become more.

00:33:44.920 --> 00:33:48.770 align:middle line:84%
And how we do that is by
letting go of our fear.

00:33:48.770 --> 00:33:50.620 align:middle line:90%
Fear is the problem.

00:33:50.620 --> 00:33:52.287 align:middle line:90%
As we let go of fear--

00:33:52.287 --> 00:33:53.995 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The unknown
as part of the fear.

00:33:53.995 --> 00:33:55.912 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Yeah, The
unknown is part of fear.

00:33:55.912 --> 00:33:57.310 align:middle line:90%
People fear the unknown.

00:33:57.310 --> 00:33:59.890 align:middle line:84%
That's part of their fear
of death, and part of that's

00:33:59.890 --> 00:34:01.270 align:middle line:90%
a fear of the unknown.

00:34:01.270 --> 00:34:03.550 align:middle line:84%
But they fear all sorts
of personal things, too.

00:34:03.550 --> 00:34:05.140 align:middle line:84%
They fear that they
are inadequate,

00:34:05.140 --> 00:34:07.750 align:middle line:84%
that they're not good enough,
that they are unlovable,

00:34:07.750 --> 00:34:11.290 align:middle line:84%
that they need to pretend
to be somebody else in order

00:34:11.290 --> 00:34:12.760 align:middle line:90%
to be liked.

00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:16.179 align:middle line:84%
So they live in an image
rather than being authentic.

00:34:16.179 --> 00:34:18.400 align:middle line:84%
So we have lots
of, lots of fears,

00:34:18.400 --> 00:34:21.100 align:middle line:84%
and those fears
inform our choices.

00:34:21.100 --> 00:34:24.190 align:middle line:84%
And we need to, basically,
take ourselves back,

00:34:24.190 --> 00:34:26.290 align:middle line:90%
if you will, from those fears.

00:34:26.290 --> 00:34:30.639 align:middle line:84%
And as we get rid of the fear,
life becomes more about others

00:34:30.639 --> 00:34:31.929 align:middle line:90%
and less about us.

00:34:31.929 --> 00:34:33.670 align:middle line:90%
Fear is very self-referential.

00:34:33.670 --> 00:34:35.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:34:35.080 --> 00:34:39.520 align:middle line:84%
Why does it seem that
when you're born,

00:34:39.520 --> 00:34:42.710 align:middle line:84%
and we develop these
different traits,

00:34:42.710 --> 00:34:44.900 align:middle line:84%
that nobody teaches
us this, what

00:34:44.900 --> 00:34:46.520 align:middle line:90%
you're talking about today?

00:34:46.520 --> 00:34:49.540 align:middle line:84%
Is this something that we
just inherit and pick up?

00:34:49.540 --> 00:34:51.949 align:middle line:84%
Is it part of our
genetic makeup?

00:34:51.949 --> 00:34:55.940 align:middle line:84%
Or do we really learn it
from outside exposure?

00:34:55.940 --> 00:34:58.550 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: Well, the reason
that it's so hard to teach

00:34:58.550 --> 00:35:02.210 align:middle line:84%
is you can't teach
somebody how to grow up.

00:35:02.210 --> 00:35:04.297 align:middle line:84%
You can't teach
somebody how to be.

00:35:04.297 --> 00:35:05.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or to love.

00:35:05.130 --> 00:35:06.530 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: Yeah, or to love.

00:35:06.530 --> 00:35:08.250 align:middle line:90%
Those things are hard to teach.

00:35:08.250 --> 00:35:09.990 align:middle line:90%
It's something that you are.

00:35:09.990 --> 00:35:11.510 align:middle line:90%
It's a matter of being.

00:35:11.510 --> 00:35:13.770 align:middle line:90%
So you have to change yourself.

00:35:13.770 --> 00:35:16.280 align:middle line:84%
Nobody else can come
in and change you.

00:35:16.280 --> 00:35:18.350 align:middle line:90%
You can't change anyone else.

00:35:18.350 --> 00:35:21.980 align:middle line:84%
You make choices, and
you do end up growing up,

00:35:21.980 --> 00:35:26.300 align:middle line:84%
one way or another, more or
less based on those choices

00:35:26.300 --> 00:35:27.720 align:middle line:84%
and the quality
of those choices.

00:35:27.720 --> 00:35:30.320 align:middle line:84%
So if those choices are
about caring, and love,

00:35:30.320 --> 00:35:32.600 align:middle line:84%
and it's about other,
not about self,

00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:34.720 align:middle line:84%
then you grow up
very positively.

00:35:34.720 --> 00:35:38.150 align:middle line:84%
If the choices are poor
choices, you don't grow up.

00:35:38.150 --> 00:35:40.460 align:middle line:90%
You stay full of fear.

00:35:40.460 --> 00:35:41.840 align:middle line:90%
Unhappy, miserable.

00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:44.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What have you
concluded, Tom, about humanity?

00:35:44.570 --> 00:35:46.980 align:middle line:90%
What direction are we headed?

00:35:46.980 --> 00:35:49.640 align:middle line:84%
>>CAMPBELL: I think that
there's a good chance

00:35:49.640 --> 00:35:52.760 align:middle line:84%
that in the next two, or
three, or four decades,

00:35:52.760 --> 00:35:57.260 align:middle line:84%
humanity will take
a giant step forward

00:35:57.260 --> 00:35:59.040 align:middle line:90%
in this evolutionary game.

00:35:59.040 --> 00:35:59.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:35:59.840 --> 00:36:00.920 align:middle line:90%
>>CAMPBELL: Yes.

00:36:00.920 --> 00:36:04.340 align:middle line:84%
And the reason for that
is, for the first time

00:36:04.340 --> 00:36:10.610 align:middle line:84%
in the history of humanity, all
the pieces are in place for us

00:36:10.610 --> 00:36:13.290 align:middle line:90%
to take a big step forward.

00:36:13.290 --> 00:36:15.680 align:middle line:84%
Now, we've been
evolving all along,

00:36:15.680 --> 00:36:17.780 align:middle line:84%
and we've had people
like the Buddha

00:36:17.780 --> 00:36:21.800 align:middle line:84%
who understood, you know,
what life was about.

00:36:21.800 --> 00:36:25.320 align:middle line:84%
And not just the Buddha,
